<p>
    They have exactly what you'd want after a day or
    four living out of a backpack and sleeping in a tent. Hot showers,
    electricity, 4G signal, toilets, a small shop
    and even a bar. 
</p>

<!-- <img class="floatLeft" src="images/location/basar-0.jpg"/> -->
<p>
    The shop sells hot dogs, grilled sandwiches,
    snacks and a limited amount of spare camping bits.</p>
<p>
    You won't be able to buy a new sleeping bag there, but they may
    sell you a pair of thick woolly socks when you discover that your
    H&M ankle socks aren't quite cutting it.
</p>
